Quikie
by アシカス » Wed 04.07.2010 2:18 am Hi,　I just wanted to make sur ethis was right, as I'm putting it in my speech for school：ひるごはんをたべることがで前に、レベッカにプレゼントをあげました。Does it mean:　Before eating luｎch, we gave Rebecca presents.　？？　Also, is there a way that　I could make it say:　Before we could eat lunch, we had to give Rebecca presents.？Thanks for the help!
アシカス
Posts: 10Joined: Mon 11.30.2009 3:01 am
