Re: Quikie
by Hyperworm » Wed 04.07.2010 9:35 am Be aware of nuances in play here though.The English versionBefore we could eat lunch, we had to give Rebecca presents.can be interpreted as eitherBefore lunchtime came around, there still remained the matter of giving Rebecca presents.(speaking with reference to the day's schedule; fairly neutral) orBefore we were allowed to eat lunch, we were required to give Rebecca presents.(implies that you did not want to give Rebecca presents or that you are only doing it to get lunch)Personally I can't help but read the Japanese versionひるごはんをたべさせてもらえる前に、レベッカにプレゼントをあげなければならなかった。as the second one...
fun translation snippets | need something translated?BTC@1KMZXgoWiDshQis5Z7feCx8jaiP4QAB2ks
